---
title: Tax Burden Shifting from Businesses to Homeowners
url: http://stateimpact.npr.org/ohio/2014/06/30/how-the-school-tax-burden-has-shifted-since-1991/
---
Since 1991 homeowners and farmers have slowly felt an increase in their tax dollars being used to fund Ohio&rsquo;s school system. In 2007 close to 70 percent of the money used to support local schools came from homeowners and farmers, a dramatic increase from 46 percent in 1991. The extra burden on homeowners and farmers is a result of phasing out the tax on the tangible personal property of businesses and commercial properties.
